name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: ***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Downtown Farmer’s Market located in front of the Capitol Theatre. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se llevará a cabo en el Downtown Farmer’s Market ubicado frente al Capitol Theatre. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel.***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a Johnson & Johnson mobile clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm-6pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
******All patients at this clinic will receive a $50 Visa gift card that can be used anywhere Visa is accepted.*** You will need to sign a consent form at the clinic verifying you received the gift card.  This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer or Moderna COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson*** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine only. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
